<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef">
  <CalDefFileVersion>6</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>2/19/15</Date>
    <Description>Fixed Values and removed RearParkAssistSymbols andTvrFFRewindButtonSpeeds cals that are no longer needed.</Description>
    <Author>Samer Khatib</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>3/25/2015</Date>
    <Description>Updated the default seting for AutoParkingSideOfVehicleDefault Cal from Default_Left to Default_Right based on default defined for this Cal in Section 3.4.2.3 of GIS-516 version 1.8 dated March 13, 2015 </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>1/25/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS516_SafetySystemsUI.caldef, added the following two new calibrations: 1.) RearCameraTransition and 2.) SVRFF_RewindButtonSpeeds in the latest version of the GIS-516.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>6/14/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS516_SafetySystemsUI.caldef file deleting the RearCameraTransition calibration since this calibration was confirmed to have a duplicate function as the RVS_SMART_TOW_OFF_HYSTERESIS calibration being implemented from the GIS-040. Also deleted the SVRFF_RewindButtonSpeeds calibration since this calibration was confirmed to not have a needed use case for CSM or Low Radio. Also, updated the usage field for all of the calibration in this caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Added GEM usage to all of the calibrations in the GIS516_SafetySystemsUI.caldef . Since all of these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="Because certain countries drive on different sides of the road, this cal will allow for the left or the right side searching to be the default option" Name="AutoParkingSideOfVehicleDefault" References="GIS-516 5.1.1.1*MY17" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_vfjMsG8wEeSP1-yKskOqPA</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/14/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_8FneoMATEeOEzdA9o_rOxw</EnumID>
      <Value>1</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The camera app automatically closes when the vehicle reaches a certain" Name="OverspeedValue" References="GIS-516 5.1.1.1*MY17" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
